The `conditionalDiscount` function is used only twice. It adds a level of abstraction. Let me check if it's pulling its weight... It does make the code read more declaratively in the `quote` function. I'll keep it.

The long return statement on line 36 is the main readability concern. Let me refactor it to group related terms more clearly.

